This paper is about improving the segmentation of dermoscopic images using deep learning techniques. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of color information and network architecture, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on a skin lesion segmentation challenge, which could also place it in the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
